===============================================
J784S4 Interrupt Management Device Descriptions
===============================================

Introduction
============

This chapter provides information on the Interrupt Management devices in the
J784S4 SoC.  Some System Firmware TISCI messages take device specific inputs.
This chapter provides information on the valid values for Interrupt Management
TISCI message parameters.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_ir_device_ids:

Interrupt Router Device IDs
===========================

Some System Firmware TISCI message APIs require the Interrupt Router device ID
be provided as part of the request. Based on :doc:`J784S4 Device IDs <devices>`
these are the valid Interrupt Router device IDs.

+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| Interrupt Router Device Name        |   Interrupt Router Device ID |
+=====================================+==============================+
| J784S4_DEV_MAIN2MCU_LVL_INTRTR0     |                          173 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MAIN2MCU_PLS_INTRTR0     |                          174 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_TIMESYNC_INTRTR0         |                          176 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_WKUP_GPIOMUX_INTRTR0     |                          177 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_GPIOMUX_INTRTR0          |                           10 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_CMPEVENT_INTRTR0         |                           11 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_INTR_0            |                          283 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_INTR_ROUTER_0 |                          324 |
+-------------------------------------+------------------------------+

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_main2mcu_lvl_intrtr0_input_src_list:

MAIN2MCU_LVL_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Input Sources
===================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_main2mcu_lvl_intrtr0_output_src_list:

MAIN2MCU_LVL_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Output Destinations
=========================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_main2mcu_pls_intrtr0_input_src_list:

MAIN2MCU_PLS_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Input Sources
===================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_main2mcu_pls_intrtr0_output_src_list:

MAIN2MCU_PLS_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Output Destinations
=========================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_timesync_intrtr0_input_src_list:

TIMESYNC_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Input Sources
===============================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_wkup_gpiomux_intrtr0_output_src_list:

WKUP_GPIOMUX_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Output Destinations
=========================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_gpiomux_intrtr0_input_src_list:

GPIOMUX_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Input Sources
==============================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_gpiomux_intrtr0_output_src_list:

GPIOMUX_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Output Destinations
====================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_cmpevent_intrtr0_input_src_list:

CMPEVENT_INTRTR0 Interrupt Router Input Sources
===============================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_navss0_intr_0_output_src_list:

NAVSS0_INTR_0 Interrupt Router Output Destinations
==================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_mcu_navss0_intr_router_0_input_src_list:

MCU_NAVSS0_INTR_ROUTER_0 Interrupt Router Input Sources
=======================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_ia_device_ids:

Interrupt Aggregator Device IDs
===============================

Some System Firmware TISCI message APIs require the Interrupt Aggregator device
ID be provided as part of the request. Based on :doc:`J784S4 Device IDs
<devices>` these are the valid Interrupt Aggregator device IDs.

+-------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Interrupt Aggregator Device Name    |   Interrupt Aggregator Device ID |
+=====================================+==================================+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_MODSS_INTA_0      |                              310 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_MODSS_INTA_1      |                              311 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0     |                              321 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 |                              331 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------------------------+

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_ia_vints:

Interrupt Aggregator Virtual Interrupts
=======================================

This section describes Interrupt Aggregator virtual interrupts.  The virtual
interrupts are used in interrupt management based TISCI messages.


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| Interrupt Aggregator Name           | Virtual Interrupt Range   |
+=====================================+===========================+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_MODSS_INTA_0      | 0 to 63                   |
+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_MODSS_INTA_1      | 0 to 63                   |
+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0     | 0 to 55                   |
| (**RESERVED BY SYSTEM FIRMWARE**)   |                           |
+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0     | 56 to 255                 |
+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 | 0 to 21                   |
| (**RESERVED BY SYSTEM FIRMWARE**)   |                           |
+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 | 22 to 255                 |
+-------------------------------------+---------------------------+

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_mcu_navss0_udmass_inta_0_vint_output_dst_list:

MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 Interrupt Aggregator Virtual Interrupt Destinations
============================================================================


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 |            331 |             253 | J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_INTR_ROUTER_0 | in_intr                 |                 253 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------+-----------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------+---------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 |            331 |             254 | J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_INTR_ROUTER_0 | in_intr                 |                 254 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------+-----------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------+---------------------+
| J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 |            331 |             255 | J784S4_DEV_MCU_NAVSS0_INTR_ROUTER_0 | in_intr                 |                 255 |
+-------------------------------------+----------------+-----------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------+---------------------+

.. _pub_soc_j784s4_global_events:

Global Events
=============

This section describes J784S4 global events.  The global events are used in
interrupt management based TISCI messages.


.. warning::

    Resources marked as reserved for use by TIFS **cannot** be assigned to a
    host within the RM Board Configuration resource assignment array.  The RM
    Board Configuration is rejected if an overlap with a reserved resource is
    detected.

+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| Global Event Name                 | Global Event Range   |
+===================================+======================+
| NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 SEVT         | 0 to 55              |
| (**RESERVED BY SYSTEM FIRMWARE**) |                      |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 SEVT         | 56 to 4607           |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 SEVT     | 16384 to 16405       |
| (**RESERVED BY SYSTEM FIRMWARE**) |                      |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 SEVT     | 16406 to 17919       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_MODSS_INTA_0 SEVT          | 20480 to 21503       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_MODSS_INTA_1 SEVT          | 22528 to 23551       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 MEVT         | 32768 to 33279       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 MEVT     | 34816 to 34943       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 GEVT         | 36864 to 37375       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| MCU_NAVSS0_UDMASS_INTA_0 GEVT     | 39936 to 40191       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_UDMAP_0 TRIGGER            | 49152 to 50175       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| NAVSS0_BCDMA_0 TRIGGER            | 50176 to 50271       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
| MCU_NAVSS0_UDMAP_0 TRIGGER        | 56320 to 56575       |
+-----------------------------------+----------------------+
